DataElement.preferredName: Bone Marrow Blast Cell Change from Baseline Percent
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Percentage of change in bone marrow blast cell measurement or assessment from the baseline evaluation [manually curated].

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Bone Marrow Blast Cell Outcome
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to the medical procedure that involves testing a sample bone marrow,the soft, sponge-like tissue in the center of bones that produces blood cells and platelets, for blast cells, immature (undifferentiated) cells occurring before the appearance of the definitive characteristics exhibited by fully differentiated cells.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredDefinition: The soft, sponge-like tissue in the center of bones that produces white blood cells, red blood cells, and platelets.:Immature blood cells.:Outcome; a phenomenon that follows and is caused by some previous phenomenon.

Concepts.definition: The tissue occupying the spaces of bone. It consists of blood vessel sinuses and a network of hematopoietic cells which give rise to the red cells, white cells, and megakaryocytes.
A precursor cell which gives rise to a fully differentiated cell of hematopoietic lineage.

ValueDomain.preferredName: Cell Count Change from Baseline Percent
ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: Percentage of change in a cell count measurement or assessment from the baseline evaluation.

ConceptualDomain.preferredDefinition: the response criteria (includes RECIST and others) and associated documentation of disease.
